KATSINA – The Katsina State Police command has confirmed the killing of five Police officers and three civilians in Kankara local government area of the State. Isah Gambo, SP, the command’s image maker who confirmed the incident to newsmen in Katsina said eight persons lost their lives during the attack which was carried out at about 6:30pm on Wednesday. According to him, the victims include five policemen and three civilians, adding that, the police officers were from the Kano state command on special duties to the area. “The Terrorists numbering more than 200 riding on motorcycles, and armed with AK-47 rifles, among other weapons was said to have carried out the attack at Gatikawa village of Kankara LGA at about 6:30pm on Wednesday”. They were said to have operated for more than an hour, moving from house to house looting food items, money and other valuables. SP Isah Gambo however maintained that, investigations are on going to unravel the incident.